  "name": "Colorectal Cancer - Chemotherapy Medication Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find colorectal cancer patients via FOLFOX/FOLFIRI chemotherapy regimens. Standard CRC chemotherapy: 5-FU + leucovorin + oxaliplatin (FOLFOX), 5-FU + leucovorin + irinotecan (FOLFIRI), or oral capecitabine. These drugs are largely CRC-specific (5-FU/capecitabine also used in some other GI cancers, oxaliplatin is highly CRC-specific).",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed colorectal cancer chemotherapy including 5-fluorouracil, capecitabine, oxaliplatin, irinotecan, or leucovorin.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on chemo for colon cancer.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed colorectal cancer chemotherapy regimens — fluoropyrimidines (5-fluorouracil, capecitabine), platinum agent (oxaliplatin), topoisomerase inhibitor (irinotecan), and the folate analog leucovorin used as a 5-FU enhancer.",
    "expert": "I need MedicationRequest resources for any CRC chemotherapy. Use these RxNorm ingredient codes: 4492 (fluorouracil), 194000 (capecitabine), 32592 (oxaliplatin), 51499 (irinotecan), 6313 (leucovorin). Combine in a single comma-separated code search. Note 5-FU/capecitabine have some cross-indication with other GI cancers; oxaliplatin and irinotecan are highly CRC-specific."
  },
